ENTRY            F0914   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0914001   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 10         24
TITLE      Investigation of highly excited states of 48Ti for
           inelastic alpha-particle scattering
AUTHOR     (A.E.Antropov,V.P.Gusev,P.P.Zarubin,A.V.Smirnov)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSSUL)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,44,(3),186,1980) English translation
           (J,IZV,44,657,1980) - relative data
           (J,BAS,46,(1),169,1982) English translation
           (J,IZV,46,(1),192,1982) - normalised data
REL-REF    (O,F0893001,A.E.Antropov+,J,BAS,46,(1),169,1982) -
            48Ti(alpha,p) reaction
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4RUSSUL)
DETECTOR   (TELES,SIBAR) Telescope consisted of two silicon
           surface barrier detectors. Detector with the thickness
           of 16.8+ -0.5 um was used as dE counter and detector
           with the thickness of 250 um was used as E counter.
SAMPLE     (22-TI-48,ENR=0.978) The 48Ti target was a self-
           supporting foil with the thickness of 0.5 mg/cm2,
           enriched in 48Ti to 97.8%.
METHOD     (EDE)
HISTORY    (20080211C)
           (20160406A) REFERENCE, FACILITY were corrected, EN-SEC
           was added. In sub 002, 003 data presentation was
           corrected. In sub 003 E->E-EXC, E-ERR-DIG->MISC-ERR.
           (20251227U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              24
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
       24.1
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           31
SUBENT        F0914002   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  4          6
REACTION   (22-TI-48(A,INL)22-TI-48,ICL,DA/DE,A/RSD,REL)
           No information about units.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Uncertainty includes both statistical errors
           and the monitoring uncertainty.
STATUS     (CURVE,,A.E.Antropov+,J,BAS,44,(3),186,1980) Fig.3
HISTORY    (20251227U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               6
